_**This post is part of our special coverage of[Bahrain Protests
2011](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/bahrain-
protests-2011/).**_

After the dawn raid at Lulu Roundabout, the focal point of the anti-government
protests going on in Bahrain since February 14, 2011, many of the injured have
been rushed to the Salmaniya Hospital. Three people have died so far.

The hospital in now in disarray, with a growing number of injured protesters.
Calls have been made for citizens to donate blood for the wounded.

